#: ../../source/help/getting-started/managing-members.rst:179
msgid "Deactivating Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/managing-members.rst:181
msgid ""
"A System Admin can deactivate user accounts by going to **System Console "
"> Users** for a list of all users on the server. The list can be searched"
" and filtered to make finding users easier. Click the user's role and in "
"the menu that opens, click **Deactivate**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/managing-members.rst:183
msgid ""
"When **Deactivate** is selected, the user is logged out of the system, "
"and receives an error message if they try to log back in. The user no "
"longer appears in channel member lists, and they are removed from the "
"team members list. A deactivated account can also be reactivated from the"
" System Console, in which case the user rejoins channels and teams that "
"they previously belonged to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/managing-members.rst:185
msgid ""
"Direct Message channels with deactivated users are hidden in users' "
"sidebars, but can be reopened using the **More...** button or the Channel"
" Switcher (CMD/CTRL + K)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/managing-members.rst:187
msgid ""
"Mattermost is designed as a system-of-record, so there is not an option "
"to delete users from the Mattermost system, as such an operation could "
"compromise the integrity of message archives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/managing-members.rst:189
msgid ""
